The paper focuses on developing a unified framework for training and evaluating statistical learning models over relational databases, which involves the intersection of database theory and linear algebra. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of cs.DB (Database), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Among these categories, cs.DB and cs.LG are the most likely as they are directly related to the main focus of the paper.
